image.altText: A graphic of Betty Shanks photo with newspaper clippings following her death around it.

props.synopsis: The 22-year-old's battered body was found lying in a garden with a bloodstained tram ticket still clutched in her hand. Hours earlier, she was savagely beaten and strangled to death just a few hundred metres from her family home.

title.children: Betty Shanks was killed 72 years ago today. Has Queensland's longest unsolved murder case run cold?

image.altText: Pictures of Aunty Lesley Williams with an inset of Queen Elizabeth II.

props.synopsis: Aunty Lesley Williams spent six months' wages on a deb ball gown to "come out" to a society that didn't accept her. This week, she was the first to share her story at a truth-telling inquiry.

title.children: 'I wanna look like the queen': Lesley spent six months' wages on a deb ball gown for a society that didn't accept her

image.altText: A crying man in cap is hugged by a boy whose face is obscured.

props.synopsis: Even the most cutting-edge road design would not have saved 16-year-old Ryan Kimball's life. His devastated father wants motorists' behaviour change in Queensland.

title.children: Dad 'broken' by 16-year-old son's death calls for change amid soaring Queensland road toll

image.altText: the gabba stadium

props.synopsis: Brisbane 2032 Olympics chief Andrew Liveris says the Queensland capital risks losing major cricket and AFL events to the regions without a "legacy" stadium to meet future demands.

title.children: Brisbane Olympics boss says ticket revenue a factor in stadium debate

image.altText: A large chimpanzee and a small baby chimpanzee sit together while the baby nibbles on a stick

props.synopsis: The new male chimpanzees at Rockhampton Zoo have agitated a crucial breeding female. Leakey and her bub will now be sent to Sydney Zoo to reduce tensions.

title.children: Aggressive chimp and baby to be sent to Sydney Zoo from Queensland

image.altText: E-scooter in Brisbane

image.altText: Bullets, bullet casings, shotgun shells and firearm parts on a stainless steel bench inside an airport.

image.altText: Smiling Caucasian woman in white lab coat holds fan of cards close to face each side. Purple nail polish, blonde hair tied back.

title.children: Meet 'Professor' Kylie the 'cardboard crack' dealer. Her own addiction started a few years ago

image.altText: Protesters in high-vis wearing sunglasses hold signs and march

image.altText: A young boy in burns wraps in hospital walking.

image.altText: People gather outside a hospital where there's a sign that reads "red zone".

image.altText: A man is handcuffed and walked down a street.

image.altText: Harris speaks into a microphone in front of a red American flag wearing a beige suit

image.altText: CHILD CARE Anthony Albanese, Jason Clare

image.altText: A blue board shows a photo of Epstein and Maxwell hugging, beside a series of dot-pointed text. A hand points to the photo..

image.altText: Two men stand together
